dialogue: 'There's this little Caterpie that's been hanging around my vegetable garden. I should shoo him off, but he's so darn cute. I've already named him... My vegetables are doomed.'
'Are you one of those Team Null bastards? Team Knight? Oh great, a different terrorist group. Just what we need.'
'Our gym leader Maisie will be able to protect Falnook from whatever comes for us! Team Null or that Team Knight!'
'Don’t think about leaving Falnook without having some coffee!'
'Make sure you leave Falnook before nightfall, or at least get a place to stay! The streets aren’t safe with Team Null around!'
'Juli's pretty and all, but if there was ever a fight to the death between her and Maisie, she wouldn't stand a chance. I just have a feeling.'
'Hey, who do you think is prettier? Maisie, Juli, or Ariea?'
'This morning my husband said it was 'a little muggy out,' and I went outside, and he'd put all of our mugs on the lawn... now there's Caterpie silk in all of them...'
'Juli’s totally a Team Null member in secret. But don’t worry...Maisie will save us!'
'There was some little girl selling hair dye earlier...it’s nice seeing entrepreneurship starting young!'
'There's this old house tucked away in Fomelhaut Forest that people say is haunted. I think it's just weird.'
'If you see the Croft family around, give them a helping hand would you? So many kids in one household... I don't know how that boy manages it.'
'There was somebody in a cloak over there...maybe they’re a Team Null member? Should we tell someone?'
'Are you ready for another champion theory? What if...they're behind Team Null?'
'Did you know that Maisie's a gym leader? All her Pokemon are as regal and beautiful as she is!'
'Are you sure those badges are real? They look nothing like Maisie’s badge…'
'I was attacked by Team Null, but Maisie saved me! She's the best!'
'Maisie's doing her best to protect us all from Team Null every day!'
'If you see a Null member, you need to report it, so Maisie can stop them!'
'They used to mine for super-cool minerals called star pieces and stardust in Fomelhaut Forest!'
